1-stepper-up-to-46v-2a","target":"l298n-dual-h-bridge-motor-driver-drives-2-dc-motors-or-1-stepper-up-to-46v-2a","line":44},{"title":"osepp-tb6612-motor-shield-drives-2-dc-motors-at-1p2a-per-channel","target":"osepp-tb6612-motor-shield-drives-2-dc-motors-at-1p2a-per-channel","line":44},{"title":"dk-electronics-hw-130-motor-shield-uses-l293d-at-600ma","target":"dk-electronics-hw-130-motor-shield-uses-l293d-at-600ma","line":127},{"title":"l298n-dual-h-bridge-motor-driver-drives-2-dc-motors-or-1-stepper-up-to-46v-2a","target":"l298n-dual-h-bridge-motor-driver-drives-2-dc-motors-or-1-stepper-up-to-46v-2a","line":128},{"title":"osepp-tb6612-motor-shield-drives-2-dc-motors-at-1p2a-per-channel","target":"osepp-tb6612-motor-shield-drives-2-dc-motors-at-1p2a-per-channel","line":129},{"title":"arduino-mega-2560-is-a-54-io-5v-board-with-4-hardware-uarts","target":"arduino-mega-2560-is-a-54-io-5v-board-with-4-hardware-uarts","line":130},{"title":"actuators","target":"actuators","line":133},{"title":"passives","target":"passives","line":134}],"metadata":{"description":"Discrete motor driver IC for breadboard prototyping — 600mA/ch with built-in clamp diodes (unlike L298N), DIP-16 package. Use when you want motor control without a shield","topics":["[[actuators]]","[[passives]]"],"status":"needs-test","quantity":2,"voltage":[5],"interfaces":["Digital","PWM"],"logic_level":"5V","manufacturer":"Texas Instruments","part_number":"L293D","package":"DIP-16","max_current_per_channel":"600mA continuous, 1.2A peak","motor_supply_voltage":"4.5-36V","pinout":"DIP-16 (top view, notch left):\nPin 1  → Enable 1,2 (EN12) — PWM speed control, channels 1&2\nPin 2  → Input 1 (1A) — direction control\nPin 3  → Output 1 (1Y) — motor A terminal 1\nPin 4  → GND (heat sink)\nPin 5  → GND (heat sink)\nPin 6  → Output 2 (2Y) — motor A terminal 2\nPin 7  → Input 2 (2A) — direction control\nPin 8  → VCC2 (VS) — motor supply (4.5-36V)\nPin 9  → Enable 3,4 (EN34) — PWM speed control, channels 3&4\nPin 10 → Input 3 (3A) — direction control\nPin 11 → Output 3 (3Y) — motor B terminal 1\nPin 12 → GND (heat sink)\nPin 13 → GND (heat sink)\nPin 14 → Output 4 (4Y) — motor B terminal 2\nPin 15 → Input 4 (4A) — direction control\nPin 16 → VCC1 (VSS) — logic supply (5V)\n","compatible_with":["[[arduino-mega-2560-is-a-54-io-5v-board-with-4-hardware-uarts]]","[[arduino-nano-v3-is-a-22-io-5v-board-with-atmega328p-and-mini-usb]]"],"used_in":[],"warnings":["600mA continuous per channel — check your motor's stall current","4 GND pins (4,5,12,13) also serve as heatsink — solder ALL of them, leave none floating","Voltage drop ~1.4V per direction (2.8V total) — a 6V motor gets ~3.2V"],"datasheet_url":"https://www.ti.com/lit/ds/symlink/l293d.pdf"},"task_lines":[],"tasks":{},"codeblock_ranges":[[64,75]],"key":"docs/parts/l293d-dual-h-bridge-ic-600ma-per-channel-with-built-in-diodes.md"},"smart_blocks:docs/parts/l293d-dual-h-bridge-ic-600ma-per-channel-with-built-in-diodes.md#---frontmatter---": {"path":null,"last_embed":{"hash":"13tsuko","at":1776210309788},"embeddings":{"TaylorAI/bge-micro-v2":{"vec":[-0.05896725,0.03328911,0.02713162,-0.05824671,-0.04458484,-0.00453778,-0.00369733,0.07649677,0.03162794,-0.0067391,-0.00795963,-0.07637183,0.02210934,0.02738931,0.00219868,-0.00544693,0.00645052,-0.02585612,0.01657056,0.0860993,0.11554089,-0.07886036,0.01550867,-0.01001096,0.03769397,0.0779252,0.02878872,-0.01230192,-0.00700229,-0.26169288,-0.01322581,0.02872584,0.00993532,-0.02766167,-0.07991509,-0.05998978,-0.05830818,0.00112229,-0.04410687,-0.00623255,0.05717678,-0.01003194,0.02625912,-0.05226845,0.01081545,-0.03619399,-0.06120684,-0.02839288,0.10552165,-0.04899726,0.04002907,-0.02886364,0.04217596,-0.0406731,0.00353375,0.02176179,0.00760923,0.05702354,0.03431131,0.03767594,0.03510421,0.03772959,-0.20316771,0.10216546,-0.01096656,0.05551,-0.04715871,0.0002672,0.06115083,0.13797581,-0.06049915,-0.03201642,0.03529542,0.04413246,0.01878024,-0.0511263,-0.02245686,-0.04062576,-0.01759636,-0.02